=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: 1-bromo-3-nitro-5-(trifluoromethyl)benzene -> 3-nitro-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenylboronic acid (or Bpin ester) via Miyaura borylation (B2pin2, Pd) | Step 2: Suzuki coupling of this aryl boronate with 4-bromopyridine gives 4-(3-nitro-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)pyridine | Step 3: Hydrogenate the pyridine/nitro intermediate (H2, Raney Ni or Pd under forcing conditions) to 4-(3-amino-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperidine | Step 4: Protect the aniline as the acetanilide, giving 4-(3-acetamido-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperidine | Step 5: N-methylate the piperidine nitrogen (e.g. HCHO/NaBH3CN or Eschweiler–Clarke) to 1-methyl-4-(3-acetamido-5-(trifluoromethyl)phenyl)piperidine | Step 6: Hydrolyze the acetamide to furnish CN1CCC(c2cc(N)cc(C(F)(F)F)c2)CC1.

